	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Jewish holidays</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Jewish_holidays#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Jewish_holidays#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Holidays celebrated in Judaism</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For the <a href="Gregorian_calendar" title="Gregorian calendar">Gregorian</a> dates of Jewish holidays, see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jewish_and_Israeli_holidays_2000%E2%80%932050" title="Jewish and Israeli holidays 2000–2050">Jewish and Israeli holidays 2000–2050</a>.</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:ShabbatcandlesC.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/ShabbatcandlesC.jpg/220px-ShabbatcandlesC.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="210" class="thumbimage" srcset="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/ShabbatcandlesC.jpg/330px-ShabbatcandlesC.jpg 1.5x, http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/ShabbatcandlesC.jpg/440px-ShabbatcandlesC.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1805" data-file-height="1724" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:ShabbatcandlesC.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Candles are lit on the eve of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shabbat" title="Shabbat">Jewish Sabbath</a> ("Shabbat") and on Jewish holidays.</div></div></div>
